<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,1340,1798]" pageId="23" pageNumber="275">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1341,1367]" pageId="23" pageNumber="275">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mey, E." box="[278,415,1341,1367]" pageId="23" pageNumber="275" pagination="85 - 215" refId="ref22605" refString="Mey, E. (2017) [2016] Neue Gattungen und Arten aus dem Brueelia - Komplex (Insecta, Phthiraptera, Ischnocera, Philopteridae s. l.). Rudolstadter naturhistorische Schriften, 22, 85 - 215." type="journal article" year="2017">Mey (2017)</bibRefCitation>
did not compare 
<emphasis box="[625,981,1340,1366]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="275">
Leiothrichinirmus 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mey" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[838,981,1340,1366]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Resartor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="himalayanus">himalayanus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
against 
<taxonomicName authorityName="in Leiothrichinirmus. Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2017" box="[1082,1339,1340,1367]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Brueelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="impressifrons">
<emphasis box="[1082,1339,1340,1367]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="275">Brueelia impressifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, despite placing the 
<taxonomicName authority="in Leiothrichinirmus. Gustafsson &amp; Bush (2017: 105)" authorityName="in Leiothrichinirmus. Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityPageNumber="105" authorityYear="2017" box="[283,1083,1376,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Brueelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="impressifrons">
<emphasis box="[283,472,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="275">Br. impressifrons</emphasis>
in 
<emphasis box="[509,711,1376,1402]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="275">Leiothrichinirmus</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gustafsson, D. R. &amp; Bush, S. E." box="[725,1083,1376,1403]" pageId="23" pageNumber="275" pagination="1 - 443" refId="ref22049" refString="Gustafsson, D. R. &amp; Bush, S. E. (2017) Morphological revision of the hyperdiverse Brueelia - complex (Insecta: Phthiraptera: Ischnocera: Philopteridae) with new taxa, checklists and generic key. Zootaxa, 4313 (1), 1 - 443. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4313.1.1" type="journal article" year="2017">Gustafsson &amp; Bush (2017: 105)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
placed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="in Leiothrichinirmus. Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2017" box="[1171,1360,1377,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Brueelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="impressifrons">
<emphasis box="[1171,1360,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="275">Br. impressifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Resartor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="275">Resartor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, parasitising two different subspecies of the same host species, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Blyth" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[935,1179,1412,1439]" class="Aves" family="Leiothrichidae" genus="Trochalopteron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="275" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="affine">
<emphasis box="[935,1179,1412,1439]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="275">Trochalopteron affine</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The illustration of the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mey" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[348,521,1448,1474]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Resartor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="himalayanus">
<emphasis box="[348,521,1448,1474]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="275">L. himalayanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mey, E." box="[565,742,1449,1475]" pageId="23" pageNumber="275" pagination="85 - 215" refId="ref22605" refString="Mey, E. (2017) [2016] Neue Gattungen und Arten aus dem Brueelia - Komplex (Insecta, Phthiraptera, Ischnocera, Philopteridae s. l.). Rudolstadter naturhistorische Schriften, 22, 85 - 215." type="journal article" year="2017">Mey (2017: 94)</bibRefCitation>
is not complete and appears slightly distorted. Other than the angle of the lateral margins of the mesosome, there are no differences between the genitalia of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mey" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[1216,1388,1484,1510]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Resartor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="himalayanus">
<emphasis box="[1216,1388,1484,1510]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="275">L. himalayanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and those of 
<emphasis box="[249,279,1521,1546]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="275">Re</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="in Leiothrichinirmus. Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2017" box="[293,443,1521,1547]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Brueelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="impressifrons">
<emphasis box="[293,443,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="275">impressifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that cannot be ascribed to the distortion of the specimen illustrated, the lack of detail in Mey’s illustration, or within-species variation. The only other characters mentioned in the description of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mey" baseAuthorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Resartor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="himalayanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="275">L. himalayanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refer to illustrations of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mey" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[509,780,1592,1618]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Resartor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grammatoptiliphagus">
<emphasis box="[509,780,1592,1618]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="275">L. grammatoptiliphagus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it is unclear whether these two species are so similar that the same illustration of the terminalia can serve to illustrate two species, or whether this is a mistake. In our experience, the chaetotaxy of the posterior segments differ among all species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2017" box="[1050,1148,1665,1690]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Resartor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1050,1148,1665,1690]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="275">Resartor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,1340,1798]" pageId="23" pageNumber="275">
We strongly suspect that 
<emphasis box="[479,831,1700,1726]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="275">
Leiothrichinirmus 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mey" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[688,831,1700,1726]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Resartor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="himalayanus">himalayanus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is a junior synonym of 
<emphasis box="[1097,1290,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="275">
Re. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="in Leiothrichinirmus. Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2017" box="[1140,1290,1701,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Brueelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="impressifrons">impressifrons</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, but the 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,1701,1727]" pageId="23" pageNumber="275">type</typeStatus>
material needs careful examination to confirm this hypothesis. For this reason, we consider 
<emphasis box="[1177,1363,1736,1762]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="275">
Re. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mey" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[1220,1363,1736,1762]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Resartor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="himalayanus">himalayanus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
a 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="275">species inquirenda</emphasis>
in need of redescription.
</paragraph>
